info.senderName: NWS Jacksonville (Northeast Florida and Southeast Georgia)
info.headline: Special Weather Statement issued October 12 at 6:24AM EDT by NWS Jacksonville
info.description: ...GUSTY SHOWERS WILL IMPACT NORTHERN PUTNAM COUNTY THROUGH 645 AM EDT... At 623 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers capable of producing a landspout near Hollister, or near Interlachen, moving northeast at 45 mph. HAZARD...Landspouts and wind gusts around 40 mph. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Locations impacted include... Interlachen, Bostwick, Federal Point, Bardin, Hollister, Carraway, and Mannville. LANDSPOUT...POSSIBLE MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH
info.instruction: If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 AM EDT for northeastern Florida.
